<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>vtemian - blog</title><link>https://blog.vtemian.com/</link><description>Recent content on vtemian - blog</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Wed, 18 Feb 2026 12:00:00 +0200</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://blog.vtemian.com/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>vibe-infer: Learning GPU Programming with Claude Code</title><link>https://blog.vtemian.com/post/vibe-infer/</link><pubDate>Wed, 18 Feb 2026 12:00:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://blog.vtemian.com/post/vibe-infer/</guid><description>&lt;p>Everyone has a story about how AI helped them learn something. &amp;ldquo;I asked ChatGPT to explain monads and it finally clicked.&amp;rdquo; Cool. But where&amp;rsquo;s the actual session? Where&amp;rsquo;s the messy back-and-forth where you got confused, the AI corrected you, and you iterated until understanding emerged?&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Most AI-assisted learning stories are sanitized after the fact. You get the polished takeaway, not the process. The repo is called &lt;a href="https://github.com/vtemian/vibe-infer">vibe-infer&lt;/a> and that&amp;rsquo;s intentional irony, because what happened here is the opposite of vibe coding. I wrote every line of GPU code. The AI was my tutor, not my ghostwriter.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Riding Existing Waves: My Indie Hacking Journey with Sisif.ai</title><link>https://blog.vtemian.com/talk/indie-hacking-update/</link><pubDate>Thu, 22 Jan 2026 15:00:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://blog.vtemian.com/talk/indie-hacking-update/</guid><description>&lt;p>I sold my company in late 2024. After 15 years of building production code, being CTO at QED (acquired by The Sandbox), and working with companies like Gorgias, I had one clear lesson: &lt;strong>product drives value, not technical implementation&lt;/strong>.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>So I started a side project. Something I could build and ship fast. Something that solves a real problem.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="the-side-project-sisifai">The Side Project: Sisif.ai&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>&lt;a href="https://sisif.ai">sisif.ai&lt;/a>&lt;/strong> is an AI video generation API. Text prompt in, video out. Simple.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>opencode-reskin: multi-agent CSS analysis for OpenCode</title><link>https://blog.vtemian.com/project/opencode-reskin/</link><pubDate>Fri, 02 Jan 2026 01:00:00 +0300</pubDate><guid>https://blog.vtemian.com/project/opencode-reskin/</guid><description>&lt;div class="github-stats">
